thread.title: MRP wrap: Star Roo set to miss Round 1
thread.title_full: MRP wrap: Star Roo set to miss Round 1

title: MRP wrap: Star Roo set to miss Round 1
text:
Krak in hot water for big hit 0:40 Ben Cunnington, Nathan Krakouer offered one-game suspensions after JLT Community Series incidents  58pm @rileybev Source: FOX SPORTS NORTH Melbourne midfielder Ben Cunnington is set to miss his side’s Round 1 clash with West coast after being offered a one-match ban for an incident involving Taylor Duryea over the weekend. 
Duryea was forced from the field with the blood rule after copping a knee to the head from Cunnington, which the AFL’s MRP deemed worthy of a one-week ban. 
Cunnington was ajudged to have “engaged in rough conduct” with Duryea, with the MRP grading the incident as ‘careless’ based on video evidence and a medical report from Hawthorn. Taylor Duryea was left with a blood nose after this Ben Cunnington knee. Picture: Michael Klein   
Port Adelaide’s Nathan Krakouer is also set to miss Round 1 after being offered a one-match suspension for a late bump to the head of St Kilda’s Sean Dempster. 
Krakouer was charged with rough conduct, which was careless and with medium impact. 
The Power faces a trip to the SCG to play Sydney in the opening week of the season. 
Elsewhere, Jesse Hogan can accept a $1,000 fine for umpire contact during Melbourne’s pre-season hitout with Carlton on Saturday. 
There were no suspensions to come from the AFLW, with Kaitlyn Ashmore and Emma Kearney offered reprimands for separate incidents over the weekend.
